&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re looking for an Account Manager to join our Auckland team to work on an iconic Australian and New Zealand retail brand.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Are:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Brand Agency, one of ANZ’s leading full-service retail specialist agencies and part of WPP and the Ogilvy Network.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Are:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Someone who has already gained some experience within the creative industry looking to further improve your skills and progress your career under the guidance of a highly experienced account management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Manager, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team in leading integrated campaigns and projects from conception to completion, including creative brief writing, budgeting, timeline management and shoot planning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be comfortable collaborating and driving campaigns through the production of assets and various agency disciplines (strategy, creative, production, studio) and client stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Checking the accuracy of artwork, client changes and brief.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend and drive weekly WIPs – client &amp;amp; internal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with internal stakeholders – Strategy, Creative, Production and Studio to ensure briefs are communicated and understood.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be supported by senior management to thrive in an environment that’s all about passion, work/life balance and recognition for a job well done.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend shoots along with the account management and creative team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be an excellent ambassador of our brand, demonstrating our brand values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does this mean for you?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many things that make The Brand Agency a great place to work, but we think these are worth a special mention:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Welcoming and flexible work environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Birthday Leave – a paid day off to celebrate your Birthday each year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loyalty Leave – an additional paid day off each year to celebrate your work anniversary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A market-leading Paid Parental Leave scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Program access.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote Work Arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Public Holidays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning opportunities for all employees and room to grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A diverse team of top industry talent, backed by WPP and Ogilvy’s global network and insights.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Fine Print:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this role, you must have the right to live and work in New Zealand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;If you require any accessibility adjustments during the recruitment process, please let us know: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:ogv-au-careers@ogilvy.com&quot;&gt;ogv-au-careers@ogilvy.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
