&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We are looking for an experienced and proactive Office Manager to join our busy team in Perth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;This is a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt; part-time role across three or four days per week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Please note this is an in-office position, based at reception, and requires a consistent on-site presence during working hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;You Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An exceptionally organised and detail-oriented professional with a passion for creating a seamless and supportive work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive on managing multiple priorities, anticipating needs and ensuring the smooth operation of a busy office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a natural problem-solver, a clear communicator and someone who genuinely enjoys fostering a positive workplace culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Brand Agency, WA’s most successful advertising and technology agency, is part of WPP and the Ogilvy network.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;What does this mean for you?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many things that make The Brand Agency a great place to work, but we think these are worth a special mention:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Birthday Leave:&amp;nbsp;a paid day off to celebrate your birthday each year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loyalty Leave:&amp;nbsp;an additional paid day off each year to celebrate your work anniversary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A market-leading paid parental leave scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible public holidays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to many perks and benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our Office Manager, you will be the primary point of contact for various operational aspects of the office, significantly contributing to the overall employee and client experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of the wider team and reporting to the Managing Director, you will be responsible for the day-to-day office management as well as providing high-level executive and administrative support to the leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This is an office-based role located in our Perth agency, as the position plays a key part in supporting day-to-day operations and the team environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage our front of house (including Reception) and ensure the office runs smoothly and efficiently every day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as the primary liaison with building management for all building-related matters, maintenance, and security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing office resources and supplies, including budgeting and ordering groceries, stationery, and kitchen essentials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage travel arrangements across the agency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute meetings and events: from room bookings to agency functions and client events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide executive support&amp;nbsp;to the CEO and Managing Director, as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate requires proven experience in an Office Manager, Office/ Admiinistratio

